Q: Find Minimum in Rotated Sorted Array
Question Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/find-minimum-in-rotated-sorted-array/description/
Question Explanation: Given is a rotated sorted array with unique elements and here you need to find the minimum element in O(logN).

Problem Intuition:
A rotated sorted array always has one sorted half and one half containing the rotation (minimum element).
The key observation is:

If a half is already sorted, its first element is the smallest in that half.
So, record that first element as a possible answer and continue searching only in the half where the actual minimum could still exist.

T.C: O(logN) and S.C: O(1)

Code:

class Solution {
    public int findMin(int[] arr) {
        int n = arr.length;
        int low = 0;
        int high = n-1;
        int mid = low + (high-low)/2;
        int ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        while(high >= low){
            if(arr[low] <= arr[mid] && arr[mid] <c arr[high]) {
                ans = Math.min(ans,arr[low]);
                break;
            }
            if(arr[mid] >= arr[low]) {
                ans = Math.min(ans,arr[low]);
                low = mid+1;
                }
        else {
            ans = Math.min(ans,arr[mid]);
            high = mid-1;
            }
            mid = low+(high-low)/2;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
